{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5572", "repo": "rails", "body": "Here's a point from purely practical convenience -- checking a predicate method `predicate?`  in a REPL can flood your screen (if the 'truthy' object is large). When ruby is used non-interactively this isn't an issue of course, however I think Rubyists are fairly heavy REPL users and so this aspect should be taken into consideration. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "523815d4bd3543c15100dda0"}, "issue_id": 5572, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4695927", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5572#issuecomment-4695927", "updated_at": "2012-03-26T15:01:50Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister", "login": "banister", "gravatar_id": "890f7065d081f3a735362b6a1ca74b92", "html_url": "https://github.com/banister", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/890f7065d081f3a735362b6a1ca74b92?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F73c2bf297c5aec4bcbdeb4435328c335.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 17518, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/banister/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-03-26T15:01:50Z", "id": 4695927, "owner": "rails"}
